Description: Fragment of flattened handle with a gradual curve from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay near fine purplish buff; mixed inclusions. Circular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Aristophanes. Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.55, 18. Trimmed. Close to the die Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum ABC 0089.01.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0481)
